<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

''kind'' is a lightweight schema engine for TiddlyWiki. Each type's full definition — fields, constraints, title formula, icon, namespace memberships, and stream-river display config — lives on a single tiddler. Instances are plain tiddlers marked with a `kind.type` field. No inheritance, no separate per-field tiddlers, no central registry.

!! Features

* ''Schema-as-tiddler'' — one tiddler per type, with field defs as a JSON array in `kind.fields`
* ''Discovery'' — `[all[shadows+tiddlers]has[kind.type]has[kind.fields]]` finds all type tiddlers
* ''Namespaces'' — types declare `kind.namespaces`, the active scope picks one (or all)
* ''Editor'' — 2-column form (label + input), table-style, with live validation messages
* ''Field Bar'' — auto-rendered in the stream river on every instance; configurable per type; self-disabling
* ''Creator'' — pick a type, fill fields, click Create; title computed from `kind.title-formula`
* ''Validator'' — wiki-wide report of constraint violations
* ''Type-builder'' — structured editor for type metadata + JSON textarea for fields, with live preview
* ''Cascade-palette integration'' (soft-dep) — when `rimir/cascade-palette` is installed, kind contributes ''Find by kind'', ''Find entity'', ''Create entity'', and ''Manage kinds'' root entries to the palette. The leader key ''`k`'' jumps straight into the ''Manage kinds'' drill. ''Manage kinds'' is the cascade-mode equivalent of the Type-builder tab: ''+ Create new kind…'' at the root captures a type-key and creates a stub tiddler with the type-builder's defaults; ''+ Clone existing kind…'' picks a source kind, then a text-input row captures the new type-key and clones the schema (`kind.fields` / `kind.title-formula` / `kind.stream-fields` / `kind.namespaces` copied; `kind.type` / `kind.caption` / `kind.icon` blank for the user to set). Drill into an existing kind to edit metadata (caption / icon / namespaces / title-formula / stream-fields), drill into one of its fields to rename the field key (with `kind.stream-fields` auto-sync; instance values stay under the old key) / set typed / caption / icon / cardinality / constraints (toggles for required / unique / unique:wiki; text-edit rows for min:N / max:N; +Add custom constraint…) / options / ref-types via picker sub-stages, ''+ Add field from library…'' picks from common-field defs, ''+ Add new field…'' captures a new field key and creates a row with `typed: text` so it is immediately editable (drill in to change typed / caption / constraints), DEL on a field row removes it with a confirm step, ''DEL on a kind row'' (Manage kinds top-level) removes the kind with a confirm step whose consequence text spells out how many instances would be orphaned (same as the in-drill `🗑 Delete this kind` leaf), ''Ctrl-↑ / Ctrl-↓'' reorder the focused field within `kind.fields` (the array order IS the form field order, so the move propagates to instances created after). Adding a field (either path) auto-appends the key to `kind.stream-fields` (idempotent); deleting a field also removes its key from that list. ''Live create-form preview'' — while drilled into a kind's schema, the palette splits 50/50 and the right pane renders the create-instance form (the same one ''Create entity'' shows) against a per-kind preview-draft tiddler; the form re-renders as the user edits the schema so the effect of every field change is immediately visible. ''Create entity'' opens a draft form with one row per editable field, an optional ''📋 Clone fields from existing <kind>'' drill that picks a source instance and copies its field values into the draft (computed fields and `kind.fields[].clone: skip` excluded), and a ''Save'' leaf whose name previews the computed title (e.g. `💾 Save as "test"`) or swaps to a ''⛔ Cannot save — title-formula yields empty'' row if the formula resolves to empty — the row swaps live as fields fill. ''Ref-field pickers'' also offer ''+ Create new <X>'' (drills into a nested spawn-create flow with its own Save / Clone / field-edit + Cancel via Esc; on Save the new instance is materialised AND linked into the parent's ref field; pops back to the picker with the new ref selected, supports arbitrary nesting depth via the same cascade stack) alongside the existing candidate list. Find by kind / Find entity drill kind → instance lists, with a ''live instance preview'' in the side-preview pane — auto-attached via the cascade-palette tag ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/side-preview`'' on `palette/preview/instance-view`. The preview's `ca-preview-applies` filter (`[<currentTiddler>has[kind.type]]`) matches any kind-instance row, so ↑/↓ across results updates the read-only card view live. The same preview also auto-attaches during ''+ New <Kind>'' (anchored to the draft tiddler — every field commit on the left re-renders the card on the right) and during the ''Edit fields'' action (anchored to the entity being modified).

!! Schema model

* ''Type tiddlers'' — fields `kind.type` (the key), `kind.caption`, `kind.icon`, `kind.namespaces`, `kind.title-formula`, `kind.stream-fields`, and `kind.fields` (JSON array)
* ''Field defs'' — entries inside the JSON array with `key`, `typed`, `caption`, `icon`, `constraints`, `options` (enum), `ref-types` + `cardinality` (ref)
* ''Instance tiddlers'' — any tiddler with `kind.type: <type-key>` is an instance

!! Prerequisites

TiddlyWiki ≥ 5.4.0 in Node.js server mode. No other plugin dependencies. Optional: `$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template` for the documentation hub you're reading right now.

!! Quick start

# Open the ''type-builder'' tab; create a blank type and fill its metadata
# Paste a field-list JSON (see the Examples section)
# Open the ''creator'' tab, pick the type, fill the fields, click Create
# Open the resulting tiddler in the story river — the field bar appears at the top
# Use the ''validator'' tab to scan the whole wiki for constraint violations

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="info">
<$fill $name="body">''Why a new plugin alongside `rimir/typed`?'' typed has accumulated features (3-level inheritance, separate per-field tiddlers, two ref-editor modes, ~1600 lines). kind drops everything that doesn't pay rent in TiddlyWiki's bag-of-fields model and adds namespaces. See the FAQ for details.</$fill>
